<h1>Upcoming Changes :</h1>
<h2>For Customize The Border (https://www.gta5-mods.com/maps/customize-the-border)</h2>
<h3>
- Fixed the issue of NPCs trying to dodge concrete walls<br>
- Fixed the issue of NPCs trying to change lanes on the border next to the prison (Senora)<br>
- Added an option to keep barriers always open<br>
- Added new styles for the large border<br>
- Added a (customizable) wall
</h3>

<h2>For Lonehaven Legacy (https://www.gta5-mods.com/maps/lonehaven)</h2>
<h3>
- Added decals to city buildings and road edges (to make them look less blocky)<br>
- Fixed the issue of buildings/roads flying outside of instances<br>
- Smoothed the terrain in certain areas (this should also modify collision detection)<br>
- Fixed the issue of shadows on the terrain in certain areas<br>
- Adjusted the LOD of the road next to the cemetery<br>
- Fixed the road's invisibility issue End of the railway<br>
- Fix the LOD light issue on the railway traffic lights next to the cemetery<br>
- Fix the collision issue on the stairs of the Tana mansion<br>
- Fix the water collision issue (no longer being able to walk on it)<br>
- Add grass for the spring and summer versions because, yes, the grass is no longer visible once all the leaves from the forest have fallen on it<br>
- Add new tree varieties<br>
- Fix some compatibility issues with FiveM<br>
- Add terrifying sounds<br>
- Change the name/logo/flag "West Virginia" to "West Vernon" and "Almost Heaven" to "Almost Hell" to reduce branding and name issues with FiveM<br>
- Redesign the antenna and the large bridge<br>
- Add end-of-map signage (barriers on the roads and farmer barricades for the rest)<br>
- Add props around the houses<br>
- Add Easter eggs A flashback (reward for their visit)<br>
- Added MLO (Massive Load Out)<br>
- Removed the last bits of snow (warehouse and cemetery)<br>
- Added more signage (WV & USA flags)<br>
(The vehicle pack will also be updated)
</h3>

<h2>For Lonehaven Enhanced (currently unavailable)</h2>
<h3>
- Added terrain and building occlusion (city)<br>
- Added collision detection (terrain and road) - first version<br>
- Added level of detail (terrain, road, and foliage) - first version<br>
- Refined and smoothed the city terrain
</h3>

<h2>If you have anything else to add, feel free!</h2>
